# SD-WAN and AI Edge Architecture Diagram

Paste the code block below into any Mermaid-compatible renderer.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph BRANCH["BRANCH OFFICES — SD-WAN Edge"]
        B1[Branch User\nDevice + Posture Check]
        B2[SD-WAN Edge Device\nApp-Aware Routing · QoS]
    end

    subgraph SDWAN["SD-WAN FABRIC"]
        S1[SD-WAN Orchestrator\nCentralized Policy]
        S2[Application Catalog\nAI Gateway Registered]
        S3[QoS Policy\nAI Traffic Prioritized]
        S4[SASE Policy Engine\nDevice Posture · CASB]
    end

    subgraph HUB["ENTERPRISE HUB — Data Center"]
        H1[SD-WAN Hub\nTraffic Aggregation]
        H2[AI Gateway\nAI-SVC-DMZ Zone]
        H3[Firewall\nZone Policy Enforcement]
    end

    subgraph ONPREM["ON-PREMISE AI INFRASTRUCTURE"]
        O1[RAG Engine\nAI-PROC Zone]
        O2[Vector Database\nAI-DATA Zone]
        O3[Ingestion Pipeline\nAI-INGEST Zone]
        O4[Observability\nAI-MGMT Zone]
    end

    subgraph CLOUD["PRIVATE CLOUD AI ENVIRONMENT"]
        C1[Private Cloud Interconnect\nDedicated Circuit]
        C2[Cloud AI Processing Zone\nRAG · LLM]
        C3[Cloud AI Data Zone\nVector DB Replica]
    end

    subgraph EXTERNAL["GOVERNED EXTERNAL LLM"]
        E1[Egress Proxy\nFQDN Allowlist Enforced]
        E2[Approved LLM Endpoint\nZero Data Retention · DHA Executed]
    end

    subgraph SECONDARY["SECONDARY SITE — HA"]
        DR1[Standby AI Gateway]
        DR2[Vector DB Replica\nAsync Replication]
    end

    B1 -->|Posture Check| B2
    B2 -->|App-Aware Route| S1
    S1 --- S2
    S1 --- S3
    S1 --- S4
    S4 -->|Policy Enforced Traffic| H1
    H1 --> H3
    H3 --> H2
    H2 -->|Validated Request| O1
    O1 <-->|Read Only| O2
    O3 -->|Write Only| O2
    O1 -->|Log| O4
    O4 -->|SIEM Forward| H3

    H2 <-->|Private Interconnect| C1
    C1 --> C2
    C2 <--> C3

    O1 -->|Governed Egress| E1
    E1 -->|Approved FQDN Only| E2

    H2 -.->|DNS Failover| DR1
    O2 -.->|Async Replication| DR2

    style BRANCH fill:#1e3a5f,stroke:#58a6ff,color:#c9d1d9
    style SDWAN fill:#1e3a2f,stroke:#3fb950,color:#c9d1d9
    style HUB fill:#3a1e1e,stroke:#f85149,color:#c9d1d9
    style ONPREM fill:#2a1e3a,stroke:#bc8cff,color:#c9d1d9
    style CLOUD fill:#1e2a3a,stroke:#58a6ff,color:#c9d1d9
    style EXTERNAL fill:#3a2a1e,stroke:#f0883e,color:#c9d1d9
    style SECONDARY fill:#1e3a2a,stroke:#3fb950,color:#c9d1d9
```

> **Diagram Notes:**
> - Branch users always route through SD-WAN fabric to enterprise hub — never direct to AI data zones
> - SASE policy engine enforces device posture and CASB controls at the edge
> - Private cloud interconnect is a dedicated circuit — no public internet path for AI data
> - External LLM access is strictly controlled via egress proxy with FQDN allowlist
> - Secondary site provides HA via DNS failover and async vector DB replication
> - All zone boundaries enforce firewall policy (deny-all default)